The paper deals with ontology-mediated queries, which are typically studied in the context of databases (cs.DB). The use of temporal logic and event-based semantics suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The investigation of data complexity and the identification of complexity classes suggests a connection to computational complexity theory (cs.CC) and the use of rewritings to first-order logic and its extensions suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
